            ">THE BIG ONE</h2>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <!-- THE BIG ONE contents-->

    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Biden breaks record</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-dec-14-1.jpg" alt="Biden breaks record" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">President Joe Biden <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/12/politics/biden-clemency-pardons-non-violent-crimes/index.html" target="_blank">announced</a> on Thursday a record-breaking act of compassion for a modern president. He commuted the sentences of nearly 1,500 individuals and pardoned 39 people convicted of non-violent crimes. The commutations focused on those in home confinement during the pandemic who have demonstrated rehabilitation, while the pardons included veterans, healthcare workers, and mentors (<a href="https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2024/12/12/biden-pardon-list/76942032007/" target="_blank">see the full list</a>). He stated that he would "take more steps in the weeks ahead" and continue to review clemency petitions to advance "equal justice under the law, promote public safety, support rehabilitation and reentry, and provide meaningful second chances." This historic announcement broke the previous <a href="https://www.justice.gov/pardon/pardons-granted-president-barack-h-obama-2009-2017" target="_blank">record</a> set by Barack Obama in 2017.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px);">This comes just a week after he <a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/joe-biden/joe-biden-issue-pardon-son-hunter-biden-rcna182369" target="_blank">pardoned</a> his son, which created waves of controversy from Democrats and Republicans alike. Some advocates hope for further action, including the release of people still incarcerated and hopefully commuting sentences to those on <a href="https://innocenceproject.org/petitions/urge-president-biden-commute-federal-death-row/" target="_blank">federal death row</a>.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>


    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>